In Table 2, the discharge durability was evaluated based on the following criteria:
A: No discharge problem with 10 nozzles (all nozzles) and no debris on the heater surface observed;
B: No discharge problem with 10 nozzles (all nozzles), but some debris on the heater surface observed;
C: Nozzles with no discharge problem were 7 to 9 nozzles; and
D: Nozzles with no discharge problem were 6 or less.
